            <title>[HBASE-1578] Change the name of the in-memory updates from &apos;memcache&apos; to &apos;memtable&apos; or....</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-1578</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Our map of sorted edits kept per Store is currently called memcache.  Memcache is name of a well-known app that does something else.  Also, our &apos;memcache&apos; is not a cache.  In BT its called &apos;memtable&apos;.  Lets rename it.  It&apos;ll make it easier explaining hbase.  What&apos;ll we call it?  &apos;updates&apos;, &apos;inmemory-store-edits&apos;....&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
